Mexico Beats U.S. 4-2 in Gold Cup Soccer Final as Barrera Shines

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-06-26T04:20:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-26/mexico-beats-u-s-4-2-in-gold-cup-soccer-final-as-barrera-shines.html
Pablo Barrera scored two goals to
help defending champions  Mexico  beat the U.S. 4-2 in the Gold
Cup soccer final at the  Rose Bowl  in Pasadena, California.  Barrera scored for Mexico in the 28th minute after the U.S.
took a 2-0 lead with goals from  Michael Bradley  and Landon Donovan.  Andr√©s Guardado tied the game seven minutes later and
Barrera put Mexico ahead four minutes after the break. Giovani Dos Santos added the fourth goal at 76 minutes.  Mexico now holds a 6-4 lead over the U.S. in the regional
soccer title which was started by the Confederation of North,
Central America and Caribbean Association Football in 1991.  The U.S. beat Panama 1-0 in the semifinals to reach its
fourth straight Gold Cup final. Mexico reached the championship
game after defeating Honduras 2-0 in extra time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
